sources.title: UniFi Access Point/Switch/LTE | Releases | Ubiquiti Community

articles.author: UI-Glenn
articles.description:
Overview
UniFi Access Point 6.5.37 provides better roaming for Gen2/Gen3/Gen6 APs. In this release, we have added improvements to Neighbor Report functionality for Gen2/Gen3/Gen6 APs. This new method significantly improves performance and reliability, including roaming between bands.
 
Your feedback about roaming performance specifically is appreciated as we continue work on these improvements for other AP generations. For additional changes for these and other generations, see the release post for UniFi Access Point 6.5.33.


This release is currently a Release Candidate for the Generation 2/3/4/6 models.
Improvements

Improved stability of wireless uplinks.
[UAP-Gen2/Gen3/Gen6] Improve client connection and wireless uplink stability.
[Gen2/Gen3/Gen6] Improved neighbor report reliability …
articles.title: UniFi Access Point 6.5.37

articles.author: UI-Glenn
articles.description:
Improvements

Update the boot animation logo for USW-Pro, USW-Enterprise and USW-PoE, USW-MC, USP-RPS, and USP-PDU-Pro models.
[USW-Flex] Add support for "Cycle PoE Power" during restarts.
[USW-Flex-XG] Improve compatibility with particular client NICs.
[USW-Pro] Filter out invalid temperature sensor readings.

Bugfixes

Fix incorrect requested RPS power on USW-Pro-Aggregation and USW-Enterprise-24-PoE.
Fix incorrect RPS power warning on the LCM when AC power is recovered.
[USW-Flex-XG] Fix the issue that resulted in packet loss and unstable network connectivity.
[USW-Enterprise-8-PoE] Fix device going offline due to tons of oops files.
[USW-Enterprise-8-PoE] Fix client MAC address in the whitelist cannot get access to the internet when connecting to other ports on the switch.

Additional information

Your device built-in display may turn black or unresponsive for ~10 minutes after firmware upgrades to upgrade LCM firmware.

 
If you encounter any issues with this release, please provide us some details on your setup and include the below information:

Switch model(s)
Previous Switch release version
UniFi Network application version
articles.title: UniFi Switch 6.5.32

articles.author: UI-Glenn
articles.description:
Overview
UniFi Access Point 6.5.33 addresses issues with meshing while also improving the channel selection after an RF Scan.
This release is currently a Release Candidate for the Generation 2/3/4/6 models.
Improvements

Automatically pick the best channel after an RF Scan if the AP Radio Channel is set to Auto.
Speed up the meshing reconnection after the uplink goes through a provision/reboot/firmware update.

Bugfixes

Fix wired APs occasionally meshing with each other instead of relying on wired uplinks when SFP connections are used between switches.
[Gen2/Gen3/Gen6 models] Fix WiFi not broadcasting after boot intermittently.
[Gen4 models] Fix 5GHz WiFi disappearing occasionally after a DFS radar hit when broadcasting at 160MHz.
[Gen6 models] Fix kernel crash to improve overall stability.
[Gen6 models] Fix incorrect channel width being applied occasionally.

Additional information

Refer to the Help Center article here to determine the UniFi Access Point generation.
Update your devices by changing the Device Firmware Release Channel in the UniFi Network application to Release Candidate.
If you wish to go back to the Official release after the upgrade, change the release channel back to Official.


If you encounter any issues with this release, please provide us some details on your setup and include the below information:

AP model(s)
Previous AP release version
UniFi Network application version
